    <div class="content-panel light-grey-panel">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="small-12 columns"><h2 class="small-only-text-left text-center purple">How your TID Travel Money Card works</h2></div>
      <div class="small-12 medium-5 large-5 columns small-only-text-left text-center">
        <img src="/Media/Default/travel-money/tid-tmc-header.png">
        <a href="" class="button pink">Get your free card</a>
      </div>
      <div class="samll-12 medium-7 columns">
        <p>With no upfront card costs or hidden fees, TID’s Travel Money Card makes your money go further. By spending in the local currency, you won’t get slugged with hidden transaction or currency conversion fees when you make a purchase or withdraw cash from an ATM.</p>
        <p>Once you have received and activated your card, simply load money on using Bank Transfer or BPAY. Pick a single currency or several to lock in the exchange rate so you know exactly how much you have to spend on your holiday. You can then use your card like debit card to make purchases or withdraw cash.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  
  <div class="content-panel">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="small-12 columns"><h2 class="small-only-text-left text-center purple">Tips for using your TID Travel Money Card</h2></div>
      <div class="small-12 medium-12 large-10 large-offset-1 end columns">
        <ul class="small-block-grid-1 tips">
          <li class="text-with-img local-merchant">
            <h4>DCC - Dynamic Currency Conversion</h4>
            <p>Local merchants may ask if you’d prefer to pay in AUD or the another currency, this is called ‘DCC’ Dynamic Currency Conversion which will cost you more so always choose the local currency to avoid foreign exchange fees.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="text-with-img pre-authorisation">
            <h4>Pre-authorisation</h4>
            <p>If you need to book rental cars or hotels, be careful using your card as a security deposit. Your money can be held for up to 30 days so keep an eye on your account balance.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="text-with-img need-help">
            <h4>Need help?</h4>
            <p>From AUS, call 1800 098 231. From overseas call +44 207 649 9404. Online tid.com.au/travel-money </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
  
  
  
  
